I'm debugging a Node.js authentication service and keep getting a 401 error even though the JWT token appears valid. The token decodes correctly with jwt.verify(), but the middleware is rejecting it. Here's my middleware function:

const authMiddleware = (req, res, next) => {
  const token = req.headers.authorization?.split(' ')[1];
  if (!token) return res.status(401).json({error: 'No token'});
  try {
    const decoded = jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET);
    req.user = decoded;
    next();
  } catch (err) {
    res.status(401).json({error: 'Invalid token'});
  }
};

When I log the token and JWT_SECRET, they both look correct. The same token works fine when I test it manually with jwt.verify(). What could cause jwt.verify() to succeed in isolation but fail in the middleware?
